# Meringue Recipe (French Style)

Ingredients:
4 egg whites (room temperature)
200g granulated sugar
1 pinch of salt
1/2 tsp vanilla extract (optional)

## Instructions:
Preheat oven to 100°C (210°F). Line a baking tray with parchment paper.
In a clean, dry bowl, whisk egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, one spoon at a time, whisking until stiff, glossy peaks form.
Gently mix in vanilla if using.
Pipe or spoon meringue onto tray.
Bake for 1h30. Turn off oven, leave meringues inside to cool completely (1–2h).
Store in airtight container.
